{
  "doc_id": "8862",
  "text": "Significant progress in phage research for food safety has been made toward phage applications in foods. Several phagebased food additives have been recently approved or cleared by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA). These approvals have increased the impetus of phage research to uncover phage-mediated applications against other food-borne pathogens [CITATION_1] . It is likely that more phage products will be developed and gradually gain market acceptance by the food industry and the consumers as a means of a safe, natural, and effective prevention of food-borne diseases [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
